.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH lf 2m
.XI lf - "File's line feed style"
.SH NAME
lf \- File's line feed style
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "lf Mode"
.sp
\fBl\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
When  enabled  \fBlf\fR  indicates  that a line  feed  should be  written  out
including  the \fB\\n\fR  character.  When set then a \fB\\n\fR is included on
each line  ending.  When  clear then  \fB\\n\fR  is not  included  in the line
ending.
.SH NOTES
This mode only effects the style in which the buffer is written if
.Ht auto 2m
mode is enabled.  \fBlf\fR mode is used in conjunction with 
.Ht cr 2m 
to control the carriage return.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
